common misconception of the SS and police as stone-cold killers, they were, in fact, intoxicated with the act of murder itself. Drunk on Genocide highlights the intersections of masculinity, drinking ritual, sexual violence, and mass murder to expose the role of alcohol and celebratory ritual in the Nazi genocide of European Jews. Its surprising and disturbing findings offer a new perspective on the mindset, motivation, and mentality of killers as they prepared for, and participated in, mass extermination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAlcoholism and crimezGermany. 0aDrinking of alcoholic beverageszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xPsychological aspects. 0aMass murdererszGermanyxPsychology. 0aPolicexAlcohol usezGermany. 0aSoldiersxAlcohol usezGermany. 4aHistory. 4aMilitary History. 4aWorld War II. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh  aPerformative masculinity, alcohol and genocide, role of alcohol and sexual violence, alcohol and the holocaust,.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021 Englishz978311075408708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2021z9783110753851oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501754210zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501754210423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501754210/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  